  "local_port": 47106,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good online interior design courses?",
  "response": "There are several excellent online interior design courses that cater to different levels of experience and areas of interest. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Coursera**:\n   - **Interior Design Fundamentals** by the University of California, Irvine: This course covers essential concepts in interior design, including spatial design, aesthetics, and design principles.\n\n2. **Skillshare**:\n   - A variety of courses that focus on specific aspects of interior design, such as using color, DIY home projects, and space planning. Look for popular instructors like Genevieve Gorder or Rebecca Robeson.\n\n3. **Udemy**:\n   - **Interior Design Basics: Simple Steps to Your Dream Home**: This course focuses on the practical aspects of interior design, from space planning to color theory.\n\n4. **New York Institute of Art and Design (NYIAD)**:\n   - Offers a comprehensive Interior Design Course that includes modules on design theory, drafting, and hands-on projects, with the flexibility of learning at your own pace.\n\n5. **Berklee Online**:\n   - **Interior Design Certificate**: This certificate program covers a broad range of topics in interior design and provides a well-rounded education.\n\n6. **The Interior Design Institute**:\n   - A well-recognized course that provides in-depth learning on design theory, practical skills, and project work. It\u2019s suitable for beginners to advanced students.\n\n7. **edX**:\n   - Offers various courses related to interior design and architecture from reputable universities. Look for offerings from MIT or Harvard in foundational design principles.\n\n8. **Masterclass**:\n   - **Kelly Wearstler Teaches Interior Design**: A highly engaging course with one of the most renowned designers sharing insights into her process and principles.\n\n9. **LinkedIn Learning**:\n   - Offers a variety of courses for specific design tools and software like SketchUp, AutoCAD, and Photoshop, which are crucial for modern interior design.\n\n10. **Lynda.com**:\n    - Now part of LinkedIn Learning, it offers various courses related to interior design and relevant software training.\n\nWhen choosing a course, consider what specific skills you want to develop, your current level of expertise, and whether you're looking for a certification or a more casual learning experience.",
